A vintage 1950s style illustration showing a towering, sprawling Rube Goldberg machine made of office equipment - filing cabinets, rotary phones, pneumatic tubes, and card catalogs - all precariously stacked and interconnected with string, tape, and makeshift bridges. The contraption leans dangerously to one side, with small cracks appearing at the foundation, while a tiny figure in period business attire stands at the base looking up with hands on hips in exasperation. Warm sepia and muted mustard tones, crosshatch shading, mid-century advertising aesthetic with slightly weathered paper texture.
